HEADWORD: Biquintile
<hw>Bi*quin"tile</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>quintile</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>biquintile</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>An aspect of the
planets when they are distant from each other by <xex>twice the
fifth</xex> part of a great circle -- that is, twice 72
degrees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>biracial</ent>⟦br⟧
